                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/67<hi rend="superscript"
                    >16/24</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-06T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>211. My telegram No. 199, August 21, 5 p.m. Major Taylor satisfactorily concluded
                    his mission yesterday and is leaving for La Paz. Commander Webb has agreement
                    with Navy staff but for some details which he will attend to at Valparaiso at
                    once. Four items of political character I have submitted through the Foreign
                    Minister who assures me of the President’s sympathetic reaction and promises an
                    answer in a day or so. I have written Welles in detail<note n="76"
                        xml:id="d71fn1">Letter not found in Department files.</note> and the minutes
                    of all conversations when translated will be sent in a week.<note n="77"
                        xml:id="d71fn2">Not found in Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
